BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blue-ridge-labs-founder-fellowship-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260519T143959Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260503
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260504
SUMMARY:Deadline: Blue Ridge Labs Founder Fellowship 2026
DESCRIPTION:Founder fellowship for early-stage or new founders tackling pro
 blems in Robin Hood's five economic-mobility focus areas: Education\, Fina
 ncial Empowerment\, Health\, Housing\, and Hunger & Jobs. Applicants need 
 lived or learned experience with the challenges they propose to address. N
 o prototype or co-founder required at application. Approximately 25 founde
 rs advance from Phase 1 to Phase 2. Open to US applicants only\; no reloca
 tion expected for Phase 1\, but Phase 2 requires in-person time at the BRL
  Lab in Brooklyn. Apply via the Airtable application form linked from the 
 Robin Hood page\; submit an idea summary and background. Fellowship is ful
 ly funded by Robin Hood (no application fee\, no equity stake disclosed). 
 Note: this is a startup/entrepreneur-style fellowship rather than an arts/
 research fellowship\; applicants should be building venture-track ideas ti
 ed to economic mobility outcomes.\n\nOrganisation: Robin Hood (via Blue Ri
 dge Labs venture studio)\nLocation: United States (Phase 1 virtual\; Phase
  2 in-person at BRL Lab in Brooklyn\, NYC)\nAward: $20\,000 stipend in Pha
 se 2 to support MVP development. No equity terms mentioned. Includes weekl
 y mentorship and coaching\, workshops on product\, growth and fundraising\
 , co-working space at BRL Lab Brooklyn\, access to the Design Insights Gro
 up (DIG) community for user testing\, and network introductions across tec
 h\, philanthropy and policy.\nDuration: Phase 1 (Explore & Test): 6 to 8 w
 eeks\, June to July 2026\, virtual-first. Phase 2 (Build MVP): 10 to 12 we
 eks\, September to November 2026\, in-person Brooklyn.\n\nMore: https://ro
 binhood.org/our-work/blue-ridge-labs/founder-fellowship/
URL:https://robinhood.org/our-work/blue-ridge-labs/founder-fellowship/
LOCATION:United States (Phase 1 virtual\; Phase 2 in-person at BRL Lab in B
 rooklyn\, NYC)
END:VEVENT
